'''Makerere University School of Public Health''' (MUSPH) is one of the schools that constitute the [[Makerere University College of Health Sciences]] (MUCHS). The schools are:

* [[Makerere University School of Biomedical Sciences]] (MUSBS)
* [[Makerere University School of Health Sciences]] (MUSHS)
* [[Makerere University School of Medicine]] (MUSM)
* Makerere University School of Public Health (MUSPH)

==Location==
The school is located on Mulago Hill, adjacent to [[Mulago Hospital|Mulago Hospital Complex]], and the other three schools within the Makerere University College of Health Sciences. The coordinates of the school are:00 20 16N, 32 34 38E (Latitude:0.3376; Longitude:32.5772).

==History==
The origins of the school date back to 1957 when the '''Department of Preventive Medicine''' was established at [[Makerere University Medical School]]. In 1975, the department was elevated to '''Makerere Institute of Public Health''' and moved to a new five-story building of its own. The Institute was elevated to a full-fledged School of Public Health and made a constituent school of the [[Makerere University College of Health Sciences]] in 2007.<ref>[http://74.125.93.132/search?q=cache:5jxRaXEAImMJ:www.phree-way.org/projects/PHREEway%2520Consultation%25201.ppt+makerere+university+school+of+public+health&cd=1&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=us History of Makerere University School of Public Health]</ref>

==Departments==
As of September 2009,  the school has the following departments:
<ref>[http://musph.org/departments.html The Departments of MUSPH]</ref>
 
* [[Department of Health Policy, Planning and Management]]
* [[Department of Epidemiology and Biostatistics]]
* [[Department of Community Health and Behavioural Sciences]]
* [[Department of Disease Control and Occupational Health]]
* [[Regional Centre for Quality of Health Care]]

==Undergraduate Courses==
The following undergraduate courses are offered at Makerere University School of Public Health:
<ref>[http://musph.org/programmes.html Undergraduate Courses at MUSPH]</ref>

* [[Bachelor of Environmental Health Sciences]] (BEHS) - A three year course offered in collaboration with [[Makerere University School of Biomedical Sciences]].
* [[Diploma in Public Health Nursing]] (DPHN) - A one year course offered in collaboration with [[Makerere University School of Health Sciences]].

MUSPH offers instruction in the following undergraduate programs whose qualifications are awarded by other schools within the [[Makerere University College of Health Sciences]] (MUCHS):

* [[Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery]] ([[MBChB]]) - Offered by MUSM
* [[Bachelor of Radiography]] ([[BRad]]) - Offered by MUSM
* [[Bachelor of Pharmacy]] ([[BPharm]]) - Offered by MUSBS
* [[Bachelor of Science in Nursing]] ([[BScN]]) - Offered by MUSHS
* [[Bachelor of Dental Surgery]] (BDS) - Offered by MUSHS

==Graduate Courses==
The following graduate courses are offered at Makerere University School of Public Health:
<ref>[http://musph.org/programmes.html Graduate Programs at MUSPH]</ref>

* [[Master of Public Health Nutrition]] (MPHN)
* [[Master of Health Services Research]] (MHSR)
* [[Master of Public Health]] (MPH) - Two years of full-time coursework and examinations.    
* [[Master of Public Health]] (MPH) - Three to five years of part-time coursework, a field research project and examinations.
* [[Doctor of Philosophy]] ([[PhD]]) - Three to five years of instruction, research, a field project and examinations.

